President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Idaho due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from March 6 to March 28, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Timothy B. Manner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.